{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771010029,"nonce":"rGdmhMAsxvtOxmPwafpjFW/AGms=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87qw_yR","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/205","origin":"github"},"title":"feat: add --draft-pr flag to worktree_create.sh","message":"## Problem\n\nAgents work on issues with no GitHub signal until the final PR. The human orchestrator can accidentally assign the same issue to multiple agents because there's no visible indicator of in-progress work.\n\n## Solution\n\nAdd `--draft-pr` flag to `worktree_create.sh`. When set, the script pushes the branch with an initial commit and creates a draft PR immediately after worktree creation, making work visible on GitHub right away.\n\n### For workspace worktrees:\n- Fetch issue title from GitHub\n- Generate a work plan from `.agent/templates/ISSUE_PLAN.md` into `.agent/work-plans/PLAN_ISSUE-{N}.md`\n- Commit the work plan and push\n- Create a draft PR titled \"WIP: \\\u003cissue title\\\u003e\" referencing `Closes #\u003cN\u003e`\n\n### For layer worktrees:\n- For each real git package repo in the worktree (skip symlinks)\n- Create an empty commit, push, and create a draft PR in the project repo\n- Use cross-repo issue reference in the PR body\n\n### Key design decisions:\n- All failures are non-fatal (`|| true`) — worktree creation succeeds even if `gh` auth is broken\n- Uses `--body-file` per CLAUDE.md rules\n- Workspace draft PRs include a work plan file; layer draft PRs use empty commits\n\n## Files to modify\n\n- `.agent/scripts/worktree_create.sh` — main implementation\n- `CLAUDE.md` — update worktree examples\n- `.agent/AI_RULES.md` — update worktree examples\n- `.github/copilot-instructions.md` — update worktree examples\n- `.agent/instructions/gemini-cli.instructions.md` — update worktree examples\n- `.agent/WORKFORCE_PROTOCOL.md` — update Work Visibility section\n- `.agent/scripts/README.md` — document `--draft-pr` flag\n- `CHANGELOG.md` — add entry\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}